caption: To all coffee lovers this is the coffee place to go to and its not priced like other place .  Loved the iced mocha coffee. David was great, funny,  fast, and got everything we needed very fast. Kudos to you David definitely made our experience the best in the morning.  So, after a long night out this is the happening place in the morning. Freshest fruit and just mouth watering croissant especially with orange jam. Fresh grounded coffee beans. If there is line it is worth the wait. We learned New Orleans look for the small areas away from the main tourist streets for the best food. Definitely another one to add to must have  in New Orleans.  A.Melo National Photography Gold Medalist 2021 foodie tour.

The place is ok, the sandwich is good for breakfast, but to park is a little bit difficult

After perusing the Museum of Death,  we had a few hours to kill before dinner. After walking a few blocks we ducked into this café. Very glad we did.  The place offers ice cream and coffee drinks.  My wife and I both ordered Chocolate Ice Cream.  Very few table spaces (mostly due to the 25% occupancy rule for current shutdown rules). The ice cream was very delicious.  We both enjoyed sitting down and taking our time eating our bowls of ice cream. The lady on charge was April and she was very friendly.  I would highly recommend this location.  If you are anywhere nearby,  give this place a try!

Small and inviting. Can enter from the street or through the Hotel St. Marie. I've only had the food once, I usually have cocktails here and soak up the ambiance. I've had the fried-green tomatoes and they're great. (By the way, the bartenders are super friendly!!! And the service is really efficient! Bravo to that staff). Anyhow, just talking to others who've sat beside me at the bar having a main course, I've never heard a bad review.
This place is awesome.   A small deli on the corner with friendly staff and efficient service. My sandwich wss fresh and delicious.  I wish I had discovered this place sooner!

We loved this restaurant, located on the bottom floor of the Hotel St. Marie. It was convenient for us because it was so close, but we loved it because the food was absolutely delicious!! We enjoyed a dinner there and a breakfast the next morning. Wonderful food and service both times. I believe there is seating in the courtyard of the hotel, but we enjoyed the quiet, quaint atmosphere inside the resraurant. Low lighting, candles and flowers made for a romantic setting. We  will be traveling to New Orleans from Texas again, and will be sure to return to Vacherie, and the Hotel St. Marie.

Vacherie is a lovely little cafe in the Quarter, tasty deli sandwiches, soups and salads.  The staff is always accommodating, friendly and welcoming. Knocking a star off for the lack of ambience, a little bit of background music and dimmer lighting would've been nice. The fried oysters as pictured were quite delicious.

Vacherie offers one of the best happy hours in the French Quarter. Each of the plates is $5 and they offer Draft beer flights, well cocktails, house wine, rum punch and palomas also for $5 each. Please check HH times and menu before going as things can quickly change. I've also been to Vacherie for breakfast and for dinner in the courtyard area. Thumbs up for all of those occasions.

We tried this restaurant after reading a local mom blog review of family friendly places. Ironically, we ended up sitting in a little space off the bar to take advantage of the bar happy hour specials. It was just perfect for our family of 6 to order a bunch of $5 small plates and share them all. We got to taste some authentic New Orleans food and also the most amazing sliders and fries we had in awhile!  The food came quickly and every item was absolutely delicious... I would highly recommend in particular the alligator sausage, chicken and waffles, and roast beef debris sliders with pickled red onions... Plus the waiter's recommendation of fried green tomatoes. All the sauces were so good we could drink them! Speaking of drinks, get the beer flight for the thirsty parents (or the Paloma). ;)  Truly the shining feature of the night though was how well we were taken care of by the bartender. He made our kids feel like kings and queens and was so attentive and even gave us suggestions for inexpensive family friendly activities to do while in town. Best waiter service we've had!

This restaurant is legit. I was wandering in the different dishes. The waitress, Abby, suggested I go with the pecan chicken. Needless to say, it was fantastic! The pecan gravy over top of it is delicious. Depending on where you're from, the chicken will be either good or very good. Bring from Iowa, I could get the same quality chicken in a breast twice the serving size. Don't let that dissuade you, very tasty!  My wife had the fried chicken biscuit with a house salad and was satisfied with the size and taste. For dessert we had the pecan pie.... Wow is all I can say. My wife are nearly as much as I did and she didn't think she liked pecan flavored anything before that.  If you're in the french quarter, give this place a shot, you will definitely NOT be disappointed.

Went in on December 23rd, the night before the Saints retired the Falcons for the season. We had the Reveillon dinner. Good choices but the food was very disappointing. At one point even, the waiter had served one course to half of our party (who politely waited for all to be served) then moved to another table to begin taking their orders. That was actually worse than not serving anyone would have been.  The hard desserts were served straight from their extended stay in the coldest part of the fridge (not appropriate to the desserts) and the coffee was scorched (I love me some CDM, French Market, and other coffee and chicory - so don't think me a light weight; I get New Orleans coffee. We were honestly blown away at just how great an experience Vacherie was. Our first visit, we went for their NYE fixed price dinner with only moderate expectations based on the price and it being a hotel restaurant (often hit or miss places). We started at the bar for an exceptional $5 happy hour--perfect Pimms cups. Restaurant has great ambiance with very attentive and friendly service (Paul). The seafood gumbo is solid, Brussels and pork belly superb, and a gigantic portion size for the pork shank entree with the creamiest grits. All three desserts we tried were phenomenal and not too sugary which is rare for this town. Overall just wonderful. We will be back.

Really friendly and helpful staff, delicious drinks, mouthwatering food. Great ambiance and somehow after all of these amazing qualities, very affordable!
Went for breakfast, waitress took great care of us. Fruit smoothie and eggs bennie with tomato, both delicious. Highly recommend

The brussel sprouts and rib eye steak are unbelievable! The crawfish and artichoke soup was amazing. The shrimp and tomato appetizer was phenomenal. The collard greens were not my taste, but I know that everyone else really liked them. Our server seems kinda snooty, but the food made up for that.  Be warned: they don't split checks!
This was a nice quiet place to escape the noise and crowd of the French Quarter Festival. Nice selection of $5 happy hour drinks and appetizers. The alligator sausage was pretty good.
Excellent food. Decent priced. Huge portions. Great place for brunch in the French Quarter!

We stumbled upon this place looking for breakfast. The two other places the we were going to go to lines were too long. I am so glad me and my family found this place the food was so good make you want to cry because you can't finish it all. I had the pancake cornmeal top with pecans. I have never had food that delicious in my life. Only regret I have is not finding that place first  I was heading back out of New Orleans so I didn't get to try the dinner menu. Family of 4 bill came up to around 60$ but it was worth it all the food is fresh organic even the eggs and orange juice.

We had a team dinner for work here while in town for a conference. I can't say enough good things about the level of service (including planning the dinner) and the amazing quality of the food. This was some of the best NOLA style cooking I've had, and I've eaten at a lot of places in town! I'm definitely looking forward to returning to Vacherie.
Very good dining here -- went here because of convenience at our hotel St Marie.   Food was very good, psrticuladly the pork tenderloin which was outstsnding
Great breakfast, good service, lovely facility.  Really recommend for breakfast in the french quarter.
Really enjoyed everything here. Fresh food and good flavors complimented the attentive staff.
